7. Can a variable shadow another variable?
-->Yes, a variable can shadow another variable in Java. This occurs when a variable declared in a specific scope has the same name as a 
    variable declared in an outer scope, making the outer variable temporarily inaccessible within that inner scope.
    class Demo {
        int x = 100;
    
        void show() {
            int x = 50;  // shadows instance variable
            System.out.println(x);        // 50
            System.out.println(this.x);   // 100
        }
    }


